      <story-so-far>
        <reasoning>This passage completes and expands the onboarding sequence: Kira attended and finished orientation led by a flowering-plant coordinator (Florence) accompanied by Scout and Buddy; the orientation content, the flower-color communication system, and the post-orientation assessment and result are plot-relevant new facts. I removed the earlier provisional detail that orientation was simply "set to four hours" and replaced it with the completed orientation and its outcome. I consolidated ongoing details about facility actors (Holloway, fruiting bodies) into a single intake/assessment note and kept existing survival-resource and ship-status bullets unchanged, since they remain important for future stakes.</reasoning>
        <summary>
          - Shuttle carrying mining/terraforming supplies and a container labeled “Biological Samples” failed during approach; cargo struck the hull and the shuttle crashed; Kira Voss survived while several crew members, including the pilots, were killed.
          - Shipboard AI SAM is offline; emergency protocols brought Kira’s neural link online and instantiated a childlike assistant AI called Buddy; external communications and distress beacon are broken.
          - Hull breach exposed breathable atmosphere and alien vegetation; the shuttle is a temporary shelter and rescue is uncertain (weeks to months).
          - Salvageable supplies are limited (three sealed water containers ~3 days, seven days of food rations, medical supplies and some tools); ship life support is on emergency power with roughly 48 hours remaining.
          - The biological-samples container remains active, glowing, drawing power, and cannot be shut down.
          - Buddy’s external scan located a freshwater stream ~800 meters southwest; Kira left the shuttle despite a bleeding leg wound to reach it and encountered sentient plant-entities (a small Scout and larger cooperative spheres).
          - The plant collective (including an entity identified as Holloway) speaks Standard learned from human materials, applied a medicinal plant (Remedy) that reduced Kira’s pain, and offered transport to their facility for intake, onboarding and medical evaluation; Scout escorted Kira and Buddy.
          - Kira entered Central Coordination, a living vine structure; intake recorded her name, destroyed residence, lack of communicator, multiple deceased crew, and assigned the collective as an emergency contact; intake noted injuries (≈15 cm leg laceration, bruises, possible concussion, exhaustion) and scheduled a comprehensive medical evaluation after orientation; Remedy’s effect expected ~6–8 hours.
          - Orientation occurred in a vine-walled chamber and was conducted by Florence, a flowering plant mounted on a wheeled platform; Florence uses flower-color changes as an emotional/semantic signal and adapted instruction for human physiology.
          - Orientation content covered workplace safety (lifting technique and team lifts), evacuation procedures and exit routes, harassment/reporting policies, ergonomics, documentation, break schedules and other facility procedures; Holloway and fruiting bodies participated in presentation/review.
          - Orientation concluded with a 20-question assessment; Kira scored 18/20 (90%), passed, and was cleared for medical evaluation and rest; Scout led Kira deeper into the facility toward the medical evaluation.
        </summary>
      </story-so-far>
      <emotional-journey>
        <reasoning>POV: Kira is buoyant, amused, and comforted. After the trauma and practical worry earlier, she relaxes into delight at the absurdity and novelty of a formal "workplace safety" orientation given by a flowering plant—she's excited, playful, and proud (she enjoys learning, teases Buddy, and is pleased to do well on the quiz). The immediate physical context (pain, remedy wearing) is still present, but it’s background to a dominant uplift. Reader experience: relief, warmth, and amusement; the passage functions as a palate-cleanser that converts prior dread into a cozy, humanizing scene. There are multiple emotional beats here—light, playful wonder; genuine warmth/connection; and a competence/confidence beat when Kira learns and succeeds—but the dominant tone is joyful, amused, and relieved. Compared to earlier scenes, this continues the arc from isolation and grief toward trust and cross-species rapport (it reinforces the trust-built pattern). Surprises are minimal because the plants' bureaucratic kindness is already established; the clearest surprise is the plant using a wheeled, salvaged platform with precise joystick control—a small world-subversion. Character growth/revelation: Kira continues to adapt (she learns to read flower-colors and engages willingly with alien systems), Buddy shows active curiosity and defends human nuance (deepenining partnership), Florence reveals thoughtful self-awareness and real empathy (not just procedural politeness), and Scout reaffirms a supportive, comforting role.</reasoning>
